[DOCUMENT]
TITLE: GHOST Evidence Selection and Condensation Requirements
UID: GHOST-EVIDENCE-SELECTION-CONDENSATION
VERSION: 0.1
OPTIONS:
  MARKUP: Text
  AUTO_LEVELS: On
  NODE_IN_TOC: True

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 1. Purpose and Scope

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This document defines semantic document-evidence selection through A3 and document-evidence condensation through A4.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-EVIDENCE-ROOT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Evidence Selection and Condensation Scope
STATEMENT: >>>
GHOST shall classify retrieved document candidates for usefulness, retain a bounded useful subset, organize selected evidence into thematic classes, condense it into internal document context, and write the result into SuperPrompt.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SRS-FILE-TREE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-EVIDENCE-PRODUCT-NAME
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Product and Package Naming Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
The product described by this document shall be named GHOST; current Python paths may remain under ragstream.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-EVIDENCE-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-EVIDENCE-KM-PARENT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Evidence Processing Knowledge Management Parent
STATEMENT: >>>
Evidence Selection and Condensation shall be governed by the capability boundaries, shared artifacts, configuration governance, and sibling ownership defined in 40_knowledge_management.sdoc.

This document shall refine A3/A4 behavior without redefining document ingestion, retrieval/reranking, or Memory Management.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-EVIDENCE-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-EVIDENCE-TWO-STAGE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A3/A4 Functional Decomposition
STATEMENT: >>>
Evidence processing shall contain:
1. A3 usefulness classification and deterministic useful-only selection.
2. A4 thematic organization, budget selection, and final document-context condensation.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-EVIDENCE-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-EVIDENCE-BOUNDARY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Evidence Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
This document shall not own document ingestion, dense/sparse retrieval scoring, ColBERT reranking, memory-context synthesis, or final user-answer generation.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-EVIDENCE-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-EVIDENCE-AGENT-STACK
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Agent Stack Reference
STATEMENT: >>>
A3 and A4 shall consume AgentPrompt and LLMClient according to 20_agent_stack.sdoc while this document owns their concrete functional behavior and deterministic safeguards.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-EVIDENCE-ROOT

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 2. A3 Candidate Input and Preconditions

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
A3 is a document-chunk usefulness classifier after retrieval or reranking.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-ROOT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A3 Usefulness Gate
STATEMENT: >>>
A3 shall classify each bounded document candidate as useful, borderline, or discarded relative to the current request-under-evaluation.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-EVIDENCE-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-NOT-PROMPT-GATE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A3 Scope Exclusions
STATEMENT: >>>
A3 shall not act as a prompt-validity gate, garbage detector, retrieval replacement, memory merge, or final answer generator.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-SOURCE-RERANK
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Preferred Candidate Source
STATEMENT: >>>
A3 shall read candidates from sp.views_by_stage["reranked"] when that view is non-empty.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-SOURCE-RETRIEVAL
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Retrieval Candidate Fallback
STATEMENT: >>>
When the reranked view is empty, A3 shall read candidates from sp.views_by_stage["retrieval"].
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-NO-CANDIDATES
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: No-Candidate Failure
STATEMENT: >>>
When neither reranked nor retrieval candidates exist, A3 shall log the missing-candidate condition and raise an explicit runtime failure.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-CANDIDATE-CAP
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A3 Candidate Cap
STATEMENT: >>>
A3 shall process no more than the effective max_candidates value from the selected candidate view; the current constructor baseline shall be 30.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-HYDRATED
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Hydrated Candidate Dependency
STATEMENT: >>>
Every candidate shown to the A3 model shall map to a hydrated chunk in sp.base_context_chunks.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-SKIP-MISSING-CHUNK
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Missing Hydrated Chunk Handling
STATEMENT: >>>
A candidate row without a corresponding hydrated chunk shall be omitted from the evidence block and local-id mapping.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-HYDRATED

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-EVIDENCE-NONEMPTY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Evidence Block Requirement
STATEMENT: >>>
A3 shall fail explicitly when no evidence text can be built from the selected candidate rows.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-HYDRATED

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 3. A3 Prompt Construction and Identifier Isolation

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
A3 exposes compact local identifiers and sanitized text to the model.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-PROMPT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A3 Prompt Under Evaluation
STATEMENT: >>>
A3 shall construct the request-under-evaluation from the central SuperPrompt projector rather than from raw GUI text.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-PROMPT-CONTINUITY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: ActiveBrief-Aware A3 Prompt
STATEMENT: >>>
The A3 request-under-evaluation shall include current TASK/PURPOSE/CONTEXT and only the ActiveBrief continuity material permitted by the finalized relation policy.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-PROMPT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-LOCAL-IDS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A3 Local Identifier Mapping
STATEMENT: >>>
A3 shall assign one-based local chunk identifiers to model-visible evidence and shall maintain a private local-to-real identifier mapping.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-NO-REAL-ID
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Real Identifier Isolation
STATEMENT: >>>
A3 shall not require the LLM to reproduce long canonical chunk identifiers.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-LOCAL-IDS

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-EVIDENCE-ORDER
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A3 Evidence Order
STATEMENT: >>>
Model-visible evidence chunks shall preserve the selected candidate order and shall include the local identifier and rank.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-LOCAL-IDS

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-SANITIZE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A3 Structural Sanitization
STATEMENT: >>>
A3 shall sanitize line-start Markdown headings, code fences, and horizontal-rule markers inside chunk text so source content cannot compete with the outer prompt structure.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-SANITIZE-MEANING
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Sanitization Meaning Preservation
STATEMENT: >>>
A3 sanitization shall replace only structure-forming line-start markers and shall otherwise preserve the chunk meaning and text.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-SANITIZE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-REQUIRED-OUTPUT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A3 Required Output Shape
STATEMENT: >>>
A3 shall request exactly one item_decisions object containing one local chunk_id and one usefulness_label for every model-visible candidate.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-OUTPUT-LABELS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A3 Allowed Labels
STATEMENT: >>>
The only accepted A3 usefulness labels shall be useful, borderline, and discarded.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-REQUIRED-OUTPUT

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 4. A3 Agent Configuration and LLM Invocation

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
A3 uses ordinary AgentFactory resolution and the Responses API.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-CONFIG
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A3 Agent Configuration
STATEMENT: >>>
The current A3 agent shall be resolved through AgentFactory using agent_id a3_nli_gate and version 002 unless an approved version is explicitly selected.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-CONFIG-JSON
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A3 JSON Contract
STATEMENT: >>>
A3 model settings, static prompt instructions, dynamic bindings, decision target, and output schema shall be defined in its JSON configuration and external label catalog.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-CONFIG

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-MODEL-SETTINGS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A3 Model Settings Authority
STATEMENT: >>>
A3 shall use the model name and maximum output tokens from the resolved AgentPrompt configuration rather than hard-coding them in A3 run logic.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-CONFIG

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-COMPOSE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A3 Prompt Composition
STATEMENT: >>>
A3 shall pass request-under-evaluation, evidence chunks, and required-output text to AgentPrompt.compose.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-CONFIG

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-RESPONSES
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A3 Provider Path
STATEMENT: >>>
A3 shall invoke LLMClient.responses with minimal reasoning effort and a stable agent/version cache key.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-CONFIG

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-PARSE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A3 Structured Parse
STATEMENT: >>>
A3 shall parse the provider result through AgentPrompt according to the configured item root, item identifier, and usefulness enum.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-CONFIG

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-FULL-LOG-OFF
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A3 Full Logging Default
STATEMENT: >>>
Full A3 model input and raw output logging shall remain disabled in normal mode and shall execute only under an explicit developer-debug switch.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-PARSE-FAIL
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A3 Parse Failure
STATEMENT: >>>
A3 parse failure shall be logged with latency context and shall be raised rather than converted into fabricated successful decisions.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-PARSE

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 5. A3 Deterministic Decision Mapping and Selection

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
Python maps local results to real identifiers and owns final selection.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-MAP
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A3 Local-to-Real Mapping
STATEMENT: >>>
A parsed item shall affect a real chunk only when its local chunk_id exists in the current local-to-real mapping.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-IGNORE-UNKNOWN-ID
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Unknown Local Identifier
STATEMENT: >>>
A parsed item with missing or unknown local chunk identifier shall not create a decision for any real chunk.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-MAP

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-INVALID-LABEL
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Invalid Label Fallback
STATEMENT: >>>
A missing or invalid usefulness label shall be normalized to borderline.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-OUTPUT-LABELS

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-MISSING-DECISION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Missing Decision Fallback
STATEMENT: >>>
A candidate without a valid mapped model decision shall be represented as borderline in the ordered A3 decision map.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-INVALID-LABEL

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-ORDER-PRESERVE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A3 Candidate Order Preservation
STATEMENT: >>>
A3 shall preserve the incoming candidate order in its stage view and decision map regardless of returned item order.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-STATUS-DISCARDED
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Discarded Stage Status
STATEMENT: >>>
A candidate labeled discarded shall receive A3ChunkStatus.DISCARDED in the A3 stage view.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-STATUS-NONDISCARD
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Useful and Borderline Stage Status
STATEMENT: >>>
Candidates labeled useful or borderline shall receive A3ChunkStatus.SELECTED in the complete A3 stage view, while final_selection_ids shall still contain useful candidates only.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-USEFUL-ONLY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Useful-Only Final Selection
STATEMENT: >>>
A3 final_selection_ids shall contain useful identifiers only, in incoming candidate order.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-MAX-USEFUL
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Maximum Useful Limit
STATEMENT: >>>
A3 shall truncate the ordered useful identifier list to the effective useful_hard_max; the current baseline shall be 12.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-USEFUL-ONLY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-NO-MIN
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: No Minimum Useful Quota
STATEMENT: >>>
A3 shall not force a minimum useful count and the current forced minimum shall be zero.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-USEFUL-ONLY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-NO-BORDERLINE-PROMOTION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: No Borderline Promotion
STATEMENT: >>>
A3 shall not promote borderline candidates into final_selection_ids to satisfy a quota.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-USEFUL-ONLY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-ZERO-USEFUL
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Zero Useful Result
STATEMENT: >>>
A3 may validly produce an empty final_selection_ids list when no candidate is labeled useful.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-USEFUL-ONLY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-NO-SELECTION-BAND
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: No Current Selection Band
STATEMENT: >>>
The current A3 contract shall not contain a global selection_band and shall remove stale a3_selection_band data when reusing a SuperPrompt.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-NO-DUPLICATE-LABEL
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: No Duplicate Classification
STATEMENT: >>>
The current A3 output contract shall not include duplicate markers, canonical duplicate references, or duplicate-removal decisions.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-ROOT

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 6. A3 SuperPrompt Write-Back and Observability

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
A3 writes complete decisions and the useful-only working subset.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-VIEW
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A3 Stage View
STATEMENT: >>>
sp.views_by_stage["a3"] shall contain every processed candidate in original order with inherited stage score and A3 status.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-DECISIONS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A3 Decision Diagnostics
STATEMENT: >>>
sp.extras["a3_item_decisions"] shall map each processed real chunk identifier to local identifier, rank, and normalized usefulness label.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-SELECTED-EXTRAS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A3 Selected Diagnostics
STATEMENT: >>>
A3 extras shall expose selected identifiers, candidate source, candidate count, parse status, maximum useful limit, and zero forced minimum.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-STAGE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A3 Lifecycle
STATEMENT: >>>
After successful A3 write-back, sp.stage shall equal a3 and history_of_stages shall receive a3.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-PROMPT-READY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A3 Prompt Reprojection
STATEMENT: >>>
A3 shall rebuild prompt_ready through the central SuperPrompt composition path after stage write-back.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-PUBLIC-LOG
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A3 Public Summary
STATEMENT: >>>
A3 shall log a compact public summary including candidate, useful, borderline, discarded, selected, max-useful, model, and latency values.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-INTERNAL-LOG
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A3 Internal Decisions
STATEMENT: >>>
A3 may log per-chunk decisions and selected identifiers at internal visibility without exposing them as public GUI messages by default.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A3-NO-CHUNK-MUTATION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A3 Chunk Integrity
STATEMENT: >>>
A3 shall not mutate Chunk snippets, sources, spans, or persistent metadata; it shall change only stage views, selection identifiers, diagnostics, lifecycle, and prompt projection.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-ROOT

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 7. A4 Preconditions and Empty-Selection Safety

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
A4 consumes only A3-useful hydrated document chunks.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-ROOT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A4 Document Evidence Condenser
STATEMENT: >>>
A4 shall transform the bounded A3-useful document subset into one condensed internal document-context artifact.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-EVIDENCE-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-PRECONDITION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A4 Useful-Chunk Precondition
STATEMENT: >>>
A4 shall inspect the bounded A3 stage rows, A3 item decisions, and base_context_chunks to determine whether at least one useful hydrated chunk exists.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-CANDIDATE-CAP
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A4 Candidate Cap
STATEMENT: >>>
A4 shall inspect no more than the effective max_candidates value; the current constructor baseline shall be 30.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-EMPTY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A4 Empty-Selection Finalization
STATEMENT: >>>
When A3 provides zero useful hydrated chunks, A4 shall complete a controlled empty-selection state without loading A4 agent JSONs or calling an LLM.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-PRECONDITION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-EMPTY-SCTX
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Empty S_CTX_MD
STATEMENT: >>>
A4 empty-selection finalization shall set S_CTX_MD to an empty string and final_selection_ids to an empty list.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-EMPTY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-EMPTY-VIEW
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Empty A4 Stage View
STATEMENT: >>>
A4 empty-selection finalization shall create an a4 stage view that marks the available A3 rows discarded with zero score.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-EMPTY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-EMPTY-DIAG
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Empty A4 Diagnostics
STATEMENT: >>>
A4 empty-selection finalization shall record skipped status, skip reason, empty-selection budget profile, empty classes/groups, and zero effective output-token limit.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-EMPTY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-EMPTY-STAGE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Empty A4 Lifecycle
STATEMENT: >>>
A4 empty-selection finalization shall set stage a4, append a4 history, and recompose prompt_ready.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-EMPTY

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 8. A4 Configuration Loading and Seven-Step Workflow

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
The current A4 implementation is a fixed three-AgentPrompt workflow with deterministic steps between calls.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-JSON-PATHS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Exact A4 JSON Paths
STATEMENT: >>>
A4Condenser shall resolve the exact current JSON paths:
- data/agents/a4_condenser/chunk_phraser/a4_1_001.json;
- data/agents/a4_condenser/chunk_classifier/a4_2_001.json;
- data/agents/a4_condenser/final_condenser/a4_3_001.json.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-JSON-EXISTS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A4 Configuration Existence
STATEMENT: >>>
A4 shall fail explicitly when any required A4 JSON file is missing.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-JSON-PATHS

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-JSON-VALID
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A4 Configuration Parse
STATEMENT: >>>
A4 shall fail explicitly when a required A4 JSON file cannot be read or parsed.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-JSON-PATHS

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-FRESH-PROMPTS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Fresh A4 AgentPrompts
STATEMENT: >>>
A4 shall construct fresh AgentPrompt objects from all three exact configurations at the beginning of each non-empty run.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-JSON-PATHS

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-RUN-LOCAL-MUTATION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Run-Local Classifier Mutation
STATEMENT: >>>
A4 classifier option mutation shall apply only to the fresh classifier AgentPrompt for the current A4 run and shall not modify a shared factory-cached prompt.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-FRESH-PROMPTS

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-SEQUENCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A4 Seven-Step Sequence
STATEMENT: >>>
A4 shall execute in this order:
1. deterministic selected-chunk preparation;
2. Chunk Phraser call;
3. deterministic active-class validation and classifier restriction;
4. Chunk Classifier call;
5. deterministic regrouping and budget preparation;
6. Final Condenser call;
7. deterministic SuperPrompt write-back.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-HELPER
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A4 LLM Helper Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
A4LLMHelper shall own shared A4 message composition, provider invocation, provider metadata logging, and AgentPrompt parsing for the three calls.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-SEQUENCE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-DET-BOUNDARY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A4 Deterministic Helper Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
A4 deterministic helpers shall own chunk selection, local identifiers, sanitization, class validation, class mapping, grouping, budget profile, fallback package, and final write-back.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-SEQUENCE

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 9. A4 Selected-Chunk Preparation

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
A4 creates a new local evidence set from A3 useful decisions.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-SELECT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A4 Useful Selection
STATEMENT: >>>
A4 selected-chunk preparation shall retain only A3 rows whose a3_item_decisions usefulness_label equals useful and whose real identifier maps to a hydrated chunk.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-ORDER
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A4 Evidence Order
STATEMENT: >>>
A4 shall preserve A3 row order for the retained useful chunks.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-SELECT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-LOCAL-IDS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A4 Local Identifiers
STATEMENT: >>>
A4 shall assign fresh contiguous local identifiers 1..N to retained chunks and maintain local-to-real and real-to-local mappings.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-SELECT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-SOURCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A4 Evidence Provenance
STATEMENT: >>>
Each A4 selected item shall retain its real identifier, A3 rank, source path, sanitized snippet, and hydrated chunk object.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-SELECT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-SANITIZE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A4 Structural Sanitization
STATEMENT: >>>
A4 shall replace line-start Markdown headings, code fences, and horizontal rules inside prompt-visible snippets with non-structural markers.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-SELECT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-NO-SELECTED
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: No Useful Preparation Failure
STATEMENT: >>>
The normal selected-chunk preparation helper shall fail explicitly when invoked without A3 rows or without any useful hydrated chunk; the outer A4 precheck shall normally route this case to empty-selection safety.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-SELECT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-PROMPT-EVAL
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A4 Request Under Evaluation
STATEMENT: >>>
A4 shall build its request-under-evaluation from available purpose, task, and context values and shall fail when all are empty.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-SELECT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-EVIDENCE-BLOCK
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A4 Evidence Block
STATEMENT: >>>
A4 shall build one ordered evidence block containing local identifier, A3 rank, source, and sanitized chunk text for each selected item.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-SELECT

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 10. A4 Chunk Phraser and Active Class Validation

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
The first A4 model call proposes a bounded ordered thematic class set.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-PHRASER
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Chunk Phraser Call
STATEMENT: >>>
The Chunk Phraser shall receive the current request-under-evaluation and selected evidence block.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-PHRASER-OUTPUT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Chunk Phraser Output
STATEMENT: >>>
The Chunk Phraser shall return class_definitions containing class_id, class_phrase, and class_context_text.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-PHRASER

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-CLASS-COUNT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Active Class Count
STATEMENT: >>>
The A4 phraser contract shall permit one to four active classes.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-PHRASER

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-CLASS-IDS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Allowed Internal Class IDs
STATEMENT: >>>
Deterministic validation shall accept only internal class identifiers ID1, ID2, ID3, and ID4.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-PHRASER

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-CLASS-FIELDS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Non-Empty Class Fields
STATEMENT: >>>
A valid active class shall contain a non-empty class phrase and non-empty class context text.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-PHRASER

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-NO-CLASS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: No Valid Class Failure
STATEMENT: >>>
A4 shall fail explicitly when the phraser returns no valid active class.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-PHRASER

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-CLASS-ORDER
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Class Priority Order
STATEMENT: >>>
The order of validated active classes shall define their priority rank for later grouping and budget selection.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-PHRASER

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-PHRASE-MAP
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Phrase-to-ID Mapping
STATEMENT: >>>
Deterministic processing shall build exact and normalized phrase-to-internal-ID mappings for the current active classes.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-PHRASER

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-CLASSIFIER-OPTIONS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Run-Local Classifier Options
STATEMENT: >>>
The fresh classifier AgentPrompt shall be restricted to the active class phrases for the current run, with exactly one class selection per item.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-RUN-LOCAL-MUTATION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-CLASSIFIER-DEFAULT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Run-Local Classifier Default
STATEMENT: >>>
The fresh classifier AgentPrompt default may be set to the first active class phrase for the current run.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-RUN-LOCAL-MUTATION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-CLASSIFIER-LIGHT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Classifier Prompt Simplification
STATEMENT: >>>
After run-local enum preparation, the generic classifier decision-target block may be suppressed to reduce repeated prompt content while preserving parse enums.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-RUN-LOCAL-MUTATION

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 11. A4 Chunk Classifier and Deterministic Mapping

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
The second A4 call assigns every selected local chunk to one visible active class phrase.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-CLASSIFIER
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Chunk Classifier Call
STATEMENT: >>>
The Chunk Classifier shall receive the current request, selected evidence block, and active class definitions.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-CLASSIFIER-OUTPUT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Chunk Classifier Output
STATEMENT: >>>
The classifier shall return item_decisions containing local chunk_id and one class_id value represented by an active class phrase or a supported legacy active internal ID.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-CLASSIFIER

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-CLASS-RESOLVE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Classifier Class Resolution
STATEMENT: >>>
Deterministic processing shall resolve classifier values by exact active internal ID, exact active phrase, or normalized active phrase.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-CLASSIFIER

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-IGNORE-INVALID
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Invalid Class Decision
STATEMENT: >>>
A classifier item with missing local identifier, missing class value, or unresolved class value shall not become a valid assignment.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-CLASSIFIER

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-ASSIGN-COMPLETE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Complete Assignment Requirement
STATEMENT: >>>
Normal grouped mode shall require a valid class assignment for every selected local chunk.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-CLASSIFIER

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-NO-MULTI-CLASS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Single Class per Chunk
STATEMENT: >>>
Each selected local chunk shall belong to exactly one active class in normal grouped mode.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-CLASSIFIER

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 12. A4 Grouping, Budget Profiles, and Fallback

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
Deterministic processing groups assigned chunks in class-priority order and selects groups according to output allowance.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-GROUPS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Class Group Construction
STATEMENT: >>>
A4 shall construct one group per active class in active-class priority order and shall append assigned selected items to the corresponding group in original evidence order.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-NONEMPTY-GROUPS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Non-Empty Group Selection
STATEMENT: >>>
Normal grouped mode shall discard empty class groups before budget selection.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-GROUPS

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-TOKEN-LIMIT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Effective A4 Output Limit
STATEMENT: >>>
A4 shall use the caller-supplied positive effective_output_token_limit or the configured/default A4 output allowance when none is supplied or the deterministic package receives a non-positive value.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-TIGHT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Tight Budget Profile
STATEMENT: >>>
When the effective output limit is below 1200 tokens, A4 shall retain at most the highest-priority non-empty class group and mark the profile tight.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-TOKEN-LIMIT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-NARROW
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Narrow Budget Profile
STATEMENT: >>>
When the effective output limit is at least 1200 and below 1800 tokens, A4 shall retain at most the two highest-priority non-empty groups and mark the profile narrow.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-TOKEN-LIMIT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-MEDIUM
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Medium Budget Profile
STATEMENT: >>>
When the effective output limit is at least 1800 and below 2600 tokens, A4 shall retain at most the three highest-priority non-empty groups and mark the profile medium.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-TOKEN-LIMIT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-BROAD
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Broad Budget Profile
STATEMENT: >>>
When the effective output limit is at least 2600 tokens, A4 shall retain all non-empty groups and mark the profile broad.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-TOKEN-LIMIT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-BUDGET-IDS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Budget-Retained Real Identifiers
STATEMENT: >>>
The ordered final document identifiers for normal A4 condensation shall be the real chunk identifiers belonging to retained groups in group-priority and item order.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-GROUPS

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-FALLBACK-TRIGGER
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Fallback No-Grouping Trigger
STATEMENT: >>>
A4 shall enter fallback_no_grouping when classifier output is missing, incomplete, unusable, references an inactive class, leaves a selected chunk unassigned, or produces only empty groups.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-FALLBACK-CONTINUE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Fallback Continuation
STATEMENT: >>>
Fallback no-grouping shall continue to Final Condenser rather than failing the A4 run.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-FALLBACK-TRIGGER

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-FALLBACK-EVIDENCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Fallback Evidence Preservation
STATEMENT: >>>
Fallback no-grouping shall retain all selected useful chunks in their current order and shall not assume per-chunk class assignments.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-FALLBACK-TRIGGER

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-FALLBACK-LENSES
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Fallback Class Overview
STATEMENT: >>>
Fallback no-grouping shall provide the active class phrases and contexts only as collective high-level lenses over the full selected evidence set.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-FALLBACK-TRIGGER

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-FALLBACK-DIAG
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Fallback Observability
STATEMENT: >>>
Fallback no-grouping shall be marked by budget profile and warning diagnostics and shall not insert an error message into S_CTX_MD.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-FALLBACK-TRIGGER

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 13. A4 Final Condenser

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
The third A4 call produces one evidence-loyal internal document context block.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-FINAL
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Final Condenser Call
STATEMENT: >>>
The Final Condenser shall receive request-under-evaluation, selected evidence, class-group package, decision targets, and required output shape.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-FINAL-OUTPUT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Final Condenser Output
STATEMENT: >>>
The Final Condenser shall return exactly the configured s_ctx_md text field through structured JSON.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-FINAL

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-INTERNAL-CONTEXT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Internal Context Nature
STATEMENT: >>>
s_ctx_md shall be neutral internal supporting context and shall not address the user, answer the current task, or imitate a final response.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-FINAL

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-EVIDENCE-LOYAL
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Evidence Loyalty
STATEMENT: >>>
The final condenser shall stay close to the selected chunks, remove repetition and formatting noise, and shall not invent facts, requirements, recommendations, examples, or outside knowledge.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-FINAL

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-CLASS-PRIORITY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Class Priority Compression
STATEMENT: >>>
When compression is necessary, the final condenser shall preserve higher-priority class content before lower-priority class content.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-FINAL

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-NO-INTRO-CONCLUSION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: No Decorative Framing
STATEMENT: >>>
The final condenser shall not add an introduction, conclusion, motivational framing, evaluation, or decorative essay structure.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-FINAL

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-TOKEN-GUIDANCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Output Allowance Guidance
STATEMENT: >>>
The required-output text shall instruct the final condenser to keep s_ctx_md at or below approximately the effective output-token allowance.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-FINAL

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-CACHE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Shared A4 Prompt Cache Key
STATEMENT: >>>
All three A4 provider calls shall use the stable prompt cache key a4_condenser_shared_prefix.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-RESPONSES
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A4 Provider Path
STATEMENT: >>>
A4LLMHelper shall use LLMClient.responses with minimal reasoning effort and metadata return enabled.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-USAGE-LOG
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A4 Usage Logging
STATEMENT: >>>
A4LLMHelper shall log available model, status, input, cached-input, uncached-input, output, reasoning-token, and incomplete-reason data for each A4 call.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-PARSE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A4 Structured Parse
STATEMENT: >>>
Each A4 call result shall be parsed by its fresh AgentPrompt before deterministic downstream processing.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-ROOT

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 14. A4 SuperPrompt Write-Back and Rendering

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
Final deterministic processing writes the condensed document context and retained identifiers.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-NONEMPTY-SCTX
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Non-Empty Final Context
STATEMENT: >>>
Normal A4 finalization shall fail explicitly when the Final Condenser returns empty s_ctx_md.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-FINAL-OUTPUT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-WRITE-SCTX
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: S_CTX_MD Write-Back
STATEMENT: >>>
Normal A4 finalization shall write the parsed s_ctx_md into sp.S_CTX_MD.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-WRITE-IDS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A4 Final Selection IDs
