sp.final_selection_ids shall equal selected_real_ids_after_budget in deterministic order.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-VIEW
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A4 Stage View
STATEMENT: >>>
sp.views_by_stage["a4"] shall include the ordered union of budget-retained identifiers and prior final-selection identifiers, marking retained identifiers SELECTED with descending synthetic rank scores and others DISCARDED with zero score.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-STAGE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A4 Lifecycle
STATEMENT: >>>
After normal finalization, sp.stage shall equal a4 and history_of_stages shall receive a4.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-EXTRAS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A4 Diagnostics
STATEMENT: >>>
A4 extras shall record budget profile, active classes, retained groups, and effective output-token limit.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-PROMPT-READY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A4 Prompt Reprojection
STATEMENT: >>>
A4 finalization shall attempt to rebuild prompt_ready through SuperPrompt.compose_prompt_ready.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-PROJECTOR
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Condensed Evidence Rendering
STATEMENT: >>>
After A4, the central projector shall render S_CTX_MD as Retrieved Project Evidence Summary under Supporting Context and shall hide raw document chunks from the normal preview.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-NO-MEMORY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A4 Memory Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
A4 shall not read or condense raw memory candidates, MemoryContextPack, or synthesized memory context.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-A4-NO-FINAL-ANSWER
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A4 Final-Answer Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
A4 completion shall not constitute final user-answer generation.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-ROOT

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 15. Configuration, Error Handling, Traceability, and Acceptance

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
A3/A4 operational limits and model selections shall migrate to JSON while current exact behavior remains traceable.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-EVIDENCE-CONFIG-JSON
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Evidence Configuration Target
STATEMENT: >>>
A3/A4 operational tuning parameters shall be migrated to versioned JSON runtime configuration.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-EVIDENCE-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-EVIDENCE-CONFIG-FIELDS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Evidence Configuration Fields
STATEMENT: >>>
The configuration target shall include A3 candidate cap, useful maximum, A3 agent version, A3 model/token settings, A4 candidate cap, A4 output allowance, A4 budget thresholds, A4 agent versions, prompt cache key, and optional-stage enablement.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-EVIDENCE-CONFIG-JSON

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-EVIDENCE-CONFIG-BASELINE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current Evidence Defaults
STATEMENT: >>>
Until migration is complete, current constructor and deterministic baselines shall remain observable, including A3 max_candidates 30, A3 useful_hard_max 12, A4 max_candidates 30, A4 default output allowance 3000, and the implemented A4 budget thresholds.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-EVIDENCE-CONFIG-JSON

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-EVIDENCE-CONFIG-RUNTIME-MISMATCH
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Runtime-Config Wiring Truth
STATEMENT: >>>
A runtime_config value such as max_document_chunks_for_a3 or a4_condenser.max_output_tokens shall not be described as enforced unless controller/component construction or call arguments actually consume it.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-EVIDENCE-CONFIG-JSON

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-EVIDENCE-NO-FABRICATION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: No Fabricated Evidence Result
STATEMENT: >>>
A3/A4 provider failure, parse failure, missing configuration, invalid class output, or empty final context shall not be converted into invented successful evidence content.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-EVIDENCE-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-EVIDENCE-CODE-OWNERSHIP
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Evidence Code Ownership
STATEMENT: >>>
A3NLIGate, A4Condenser, A4 deterministic processing, A4LLMHelper, and their concrete JSON configurations shall map to the deepest applicable UIDs in this document.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-EVIDENCE-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-EVIDENCE-SIBLING
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Sibling Ownership Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
Retrieval/reranking scores and candidate generation shall remain owned by 42; memory filtering/synthesis shall remain outside this document.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-EVIDENCE-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-EVIDENCE-AC-A3-LABELS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: A3 Labels
STATEMENT: >>>
Given a valid A3 call, every processed candidate shall receive normalized useful, borderline, or discarded classification, with missing/invalid results represented as borderline.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-OUTPUT-LABELS

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-EVIDENCE-AC-A3-SELECT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: A3 Useful-Only Selection
STATEMENT: >>>
A3 final_selection_ids shall contain at most the configured maximum of useful candidates and shall contain no borderline or discarded identifier.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-USEFUL-ONLY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-EVIDENCE-AC-A3-ZERO
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: A3 Zero Useful
STATEMENT: >>>
Given zero useful classifications, A3 shall complete with empty final_selection_ids and A4 shall complete through empty-selection safety without an LLM call.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-ZERO-USEFUL

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-EVIDENCE-AC-LOCAL-IDS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Local Identifier Isolation
STATEMENT: >>>
A3 and A4 model-visible chunk identifiers shall be compact local identifiers and final stage artifacts shall map back to real stable chunk identifiers.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A3-LOCAL-IDS

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-EVIDENCE-AC-A4-CLASSES
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: A4 Active Classes
STATEMENT: >>>
A valid phraser result shall yield one to four active classes using allowed internal IDs with non-empty phrase and context fields.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-CLASS-COUNT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-EVIDENCE-AC-A4-GROUP
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: A4 Complete Grouping
STATEMENT: >>>
When every selected local chunk has a valid active-class assignment, A4 shall build non-empty priority-ordered groups and apply the effective budget profile.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-GROUPS

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-EVIDENCE-AC-A4-FALLBACK
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: A4 Fallback
STATEMENT: >>>
When classifier grouping is incomplete or unusable, A4 shall retain all selected chunks in original order, mark fallback_no_grouping, and continue to final condensation.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-FALLBACK-CONTINUE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-EVIDENCE-AC-A4-CONTEXT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: A4 Internal Context
STATEMENT: >>>
A successful normal A4 run shall produce non-empty S_CTX_MD that is evidence-loyal internal context and shall not be a direct user answer.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-INTERNAL-CONTEXT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-EVIDENCE-AC-A4-BUDGET
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: A4 Budget Profiles
STATEMENT: >>>
For token limits below 1200, below 1800, below 2600, and at least 2600, the retained group counts and profile names shall match tight, narrow, medium, and broad rules respectively.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-TOKEN-LIMIT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-EVIDENCE-AC-NO-MEMORY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Document-Only Evidence
STATEMENT: >>>
A3/A4 outputs shall be unchanged by the presence of raw memory candidates except through separately approved current-request/ActiveBrief input already projected before Knowledge Management.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-A4-NO-MEMORY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-EVIDENCE-AC-CONFIG
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: JSON Parameter Migration
STATEMENT: >>>
After configuration migration, evidence-stage limits, thresholds, models, and agent versions shall change through validated JSON and shall be observable without hidden Python edits.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-EVIDENCE-CONFIG-JSON

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-EVIDENCE-AC-SYNC
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Requirement-Code Synchronization
STATEMENT: >>>
An evidence-processing baseline shall not be accepted when A3 selection semantics, A4 sequence, class validation, fallback behavior, budget rules, S_CTX_MD meaning, or configuration authority contradicts this document.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-EVIDENCE-CODE-OWNERSHIP

[[/SECTION]]
